<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,868,1182]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
This subspecies was described based on 
<typeStatus box="[619,721,868,894]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">syntypes</typeStatus>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt, M." box="[891,1070,868,894]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" pagination="297 - 321" refId="ref7219" refString="Schmidt, M. (1924) Die amerikanischen Callichrominen (Col. Ceramb.) nach systematischen und phylogenetischen Gesichtspunkten dargestellt. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1924 (5), 297 - 321." type="journal article" year="1924">Schmidt (1924)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[1128,1226,868,894]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">syntypes</typeStatus>
belonged to more than one collection. Monné (2018a) reported the 
<typeStatus box="[709,807,904,930]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">syntypes</typeStatus>
being deposited in the ZMHB collection. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tavakilian, G. &amp; Chevillotte, H." pageId="11" pageNumber="531" refId="ref7297" refString="Tavakilian, G. &amp; Chevillotte, H. (2018) Titan: base de donnees internationales sur les Cerambycidae ou Longicornes. Version 3.0. Available from: http: // titan. gbif. fr / (accessed 31 January 2019)" type="url" year="2018">Tavakilian &amp; Chevillotte (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, listed them as being deposited in the MNLI collection. 
<bibRefCitation author="Napp, D. S. &amp; Martins, U. R." box="[997,1265,940,966]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" pagination="223 - 354" refId="ref7038" refString="Napp, D. S. &amp; Martins, U. R. (2009) Tribo Callichromatini. In: Martins, U. R. (org.), Cerambycidae sul-americanos (Coleoptera) Taxonomia. Vol. 10. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 223 - 354." type="book chapter" year="2009">Napp &amp; Martins (2009)</bibRefCitation>
did not inform where the 
<typeStatus box="[267,365,976,1002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">syntypes</typeStatus>
were deposited. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gaedike, H. &amp; Behne, L." box="[553,829,976,1002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" pagination="169 - 198" refId="ref5866" refString="Gaedike, H. &amp; Behne, L. (2013) Katalog der in den Sammlungen des Senckenberg Deutschen Entomologischen Instituts aufbe- wahrten Typen-Coleoptera: Cerambycidae. Beitrage zur Entomologie, 63 (1), 169 - 198." type="journal article" year="2013">Gaedike &amp; Behne (2013</bibRefCitation>
: 173) reported 
<specimenCount box="[997,1116,976,1002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">4 syntypes</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1183,1293,976,1002]" name="Colombia" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">Colombia</collectingCountry>
deposited in the DEIC collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="531" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,868,1182]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A." box="[199,365,1048,1074]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" refId="ref6797" refString="Monne, M. A. (1993) Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Western Hemisphere. Part VIII. Subfamily Cerambycinae: Tribes Saphanini, Callichromatini, Compsocerini, Rosaliini, Dryobiini and Callidiini. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, S &quot; o Paulo, 97 pp." type="book" year="1993">Monné (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, without any explanation, included 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1924" box="[780,1363,1048,1074]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Callichroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="auricomum" subGenus="Callichroma" subSpecies="viridescens">
<emphasis box="[780,921,1048,1074]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">Callichroma</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[939,1080,1048,1074]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">Callichroma</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1099,1363,1048,1074]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">auricomum viridescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[309,586,1084,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Callichroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auricomum">
<emphasis box="[309,586,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">Callichroma auricomum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Napp, D. S. &amp; Martins, U. R." box="[601,872,1084,1110]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" pagination="223 - 354" refId="ref7038" refString="Napp, D. S. &amp; Martins, U. R. (2009) Tribo Callichromatini. In: Martins, U. R. (org.), Cerambycidae sul-americanos (Coleoptera) Taxonomia. Vol. 10. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 223 - 354." type="book chapter" year="2009">Napp &amp; Martins (2009)</bibRefCitation>
only listed the synonymy, but did not provide an explanation. We accept the indication by 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A." box="[606,765,1120,1146]" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" refId="ref6797" refString="Monne, M. A. (1993) Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Western Hemisphere. Part VIII. Subfamily Cerambycinae: Tribes Saphanini, Callichromatini, Compsocerini, Rosaliini, Dryobiini and Callidiini. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, S &quot; o Paulo, 97 pp." type="book" year="1993">Monné (1993)</bibRefCitation>
as a formal synonymy (see comments on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1924" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Callichroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="auricomum" subGenus="Callichroma" subSpecies="rubescens">
<emphasis box="[1227,1253,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1268,1294,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="531">auricomum rubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
